(At temperatures of 50 to 60 degrees, tissue damage occurs. Depending on the duration and intensity of the action, reversible or permanent damage occurs. From the 20 minute) your blood rises briefly to 42.5 degrees Celsius. This kills around 80% of all viruses. Then leave the tub and try to keep the residual heat in warm and sterilized clothes! You will be better soon! If you feel dizzy, that's a good sign, but don't overdo it, not to the extent that you burn yourself. Instead repeat it every hour, three times a day (very important), which is much more effective! Consume plenty of vitamins C and D and during breaks to get rid of most viruses. However, a warm bath is much more effective to warm up your blood quickly as it allows you to transfer heat directly! You can also drink warm tea beforehand to warm the body from the inside. which I can highly recommend! It’s best not to do this alone, but under supervision, if you have other diseases! Don't do it with underlying circulatory diseases! It is best in the evening after being in public with people, for example to get food! Sterilize your bedroom with clinical gloves, They then do all daily tasks exclusively in their living room and only enter bedrooms immediately after the warm bath in the evening. The viruses will die within 24 to 48 hours after the first cleaning by not entering the room! Take the bed sheets out of the room in the morning and wash them immediately, Immediately after cleaning, pack them in sterile film with your clinical gloves and put them in your night room behind the door without entering the room! Also isolate your bedroom window frames with anti pollen material, because you need oxygen for restful sleep,
under these conditions, the viruses will not multiply and even die!

DOH Health Bulletin to the Public:

The Upper Respiratory Infection affecting China at present is quite serious. The virus causing it is very potent and is resistant to existing antibiotics.

(virus is not bacterial infection hence cannot be treated by antibiotics).

The prevention method now is to keep your throat moist, do not let your throat dry up. Thus do not hold your thirst because once your membrane in your throat is dried, the virus will invade into your body within 10 mins. Drink 50-80cc warm water, 30-50cc for kids, according to age. Everytime you feel your throat is dry, do not wait, keep water in hand. Do not drink plenty at one time as it does not help; instead, continue to keep throat moist. Till end of March, do not go to crowded places, wear mask as needed especially in train or public transportation.

Avoid fried or spicy food and load up vitamin C.

The symptoms/ description are:

1. Repeated high fever.
2. Prolonged coughing after fever.
3. Children are more prone.
4. Adults usually feel uneasy, headache and mainly respiratory related illness.

This illness is highly contagious. Let's continue to pray and wait for further notice about the infection.

Please share.
